Much as I don't like it, something involving `exec` would probably work here (given the syntax is genuinely incompatible):

Something like:

```
def __getattr__(self):
     # Python 2 version, possibly not fully solving the problem

if sys.version_info >= (3, 6):
    __getattr__ = exec("... full version as in your code...")
elif sys.version_info > (2, 7):
    __getattr__ = exec("... work round ModuleNotFoundError...")
```
